Preheat the oven to 200 degrees. Slice the @Courgette{1} into very thin discs (less than ½ cm thick). Very finely chop the @Sundried Tomatoes{2}. Very, very finely slice the @Vine Tomatoes{1}.

Heat a large #non-stick pan{} on high heat. In a #bowl{} mix the courgette slices gently with @olive oil{2%tsp}. Fry the courgettes for ~{1%minute} on each side and remove to a #plate{}. Tip: Do not overcrowd the pan - space the courgettes out to brown them off.

Mix the @Cream Cheese{4} with the sun-dried tomato and grate in half of the @Parmesan Cheese{1.5}. Tip: To loosen up the cheese add @?milk{1%tbsp} if you have it (or @?1%tbsp water{} if not).

Unroll the @Puff Pastry Sheet{1} onto a lightly greased #baking tray{} and trim the edges to form a rectangle. Using a #kitchen knife{} mark a border around the tart, 1cm from the edge.

Spread the cream cheese mixture inside the border. Place the courgette and tomato slices on top of the tart and scatter over the @Dried Oregano{1}. Sprinkle on a pinch of @salt{pinch} and a few good grinds of @black pepper{}. Tip: For a more golden finish brush the 1cm pastry border with a little milk if you have some.

Bake for ~{15-20%minutes} until the pastry has risen and is nice and golden.

Mix your @Wild Rocket{1} with @olive oil{2%tsp}(best quality) and a pinch of salt and pepper.

Scatter the rocket and remaining cheese over the cooked tart and serve it straight away. Tip: We like serving one large tart to cut at the table but you can make mini ones if you like.